<H2>6.2. PD-Tests (by Malte Mende)</H2>
<H3>SameGame</H3>
<P>
I would like to start with SameGame which impressed me really. At first I thought:
Another boaring WB game... but it is real fun.
</P>
<P>
On the screen you see a gameboard which is filled with colored balls.
</P>
<P>
You have to remove the balls by clicking on it. BUT: you can only remove a ball 
when there are at least 2 in same color side by side, vertikal or horizontal.
The more balls you remove with one click the more points you will get. 
</P>
<P>
Who removes all the balls (which is not easy!) will get 1000 extrapionts.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the game you can join the highscore list which allows a contest with 
friends or opponents.
</P>
<P>
Although there are more than 65000 gameboards the game is a bit boring in the 
long run.
</P>
<P>
The graphic is simple but good. The game is played either on a screen on the 
workbench or on a custom screen. There is no sound.
</P>
<P>
Sum: For playing only sometimes quite good.
</P>
