<H3>SpaceBall2000</H3>
<P>
Yeah! That압 freeware! This is one of these games which everybody should have.
</P>
<P>
You are a robot (or is it a human in armaments?) and playing a Pong like game 
against the computer or a friend.
</P>
<P>
Well, it is not really Pong, it is more a Shufflepuck-Cafe variant out of the bird압-
eye view.
</P>
<P>
You have to get a ball in the opponent goal which is nearly the whole upper 
border of the screen and have a look that the opponent does not get the ball into 
your goal.
You hit the ball under the law of: the angle of incidents is the angle of reflection.
Further more there are two moving girders on which the ball can rebound and 
sometimes a magnetic field changes the direction of the ball.
</P>
<P>
Seams to be complicated, but it is not.
</P>
<P>
When you have 5 goals you get further and play against the next opponent.
</P>
<P>
But if your opponent has 5 goals the game is over.
</P>
<P>
In addition to playing against the computer you can play against a friend (might be 
excellent on boring partys!) or in training modus against an impossible opponent.
</P>
<P>
The graphic is really good and attains its goal.
</P>
<P>
The FX are also good (I could sware I heard them elsewhere) and the music is nice 
and doesn앖 importunate. Nothing bombastic but good.
</P>
<P>
The game is making passionately desiring it...
</P>
<P>
Sum: You have to download it, you won앖 regrett.
</P>
