<H3>Fnurr2000</H3>
<P>
Simple games are the best. That압 an old wisdom. Following this wisdom, Richard 
Fhager as created a real simple game.
You move a dot which is pursued by another 25 dots. All dots have the same 
speed. If two dots collide they explode.
</P>
<P>
If the Players dot is in this exlosion the game is over, every other dot in the 
explosion will explode too. To get the dots exploding you just have to manage 
your pursue the right way.
</P>
<P>
The points you get is depending on the number of dots in the explosion:
three times the number of dots exploding simultaneous and a point for every 
second your dot survives. Seams a bit complicated but you앏l get it quick.
</P>
<P>
For the better ones there is a special modus activated by pressing F1. Then you will 
pursued by more points.
</P>
<P>
The graphic is quite simple, the dots are really dots, an so is the background. But 
the computer has to do a lot in the special mode.
</P>
<P>
The music in the game is very, very hectic and doesn앖 help in difficult situations
</P>
<P>
The music of the title screen is good (the other one isn앖 bad but veined;-))
</P>
<P>
In the readme file is mentioned that the game is for 5 minutes of fun. That압 true, 
but it is always fun to chase the pixel allover the screen.
 </P>
<P>
Sum: Get it, it is real fun but in the long run it gets boring.
</P>
